com.ibm.xmi.framework
Class ValueInfo

java.lang.Object
  |
  +--com.ibm.xmi.framework.ValueInfo
public class ValueInfo
extends java.lang.Object

This class holds information about a value that the framework gets when it parses an XMI file. You can query an instance of this class to get the information you need to create a value when implementing a reader adapter.

ValueInfo

Method Detail

getClassName

public java.lang.String getClassName()
For XMI 1.0, the class name for the feature is the name of the class the feature is declared in. For XMI 1.1, the class name for properties or links that are stored in XML attributes is the name of the class of the object it belongs to; otherwise, the class name is the same as for XMI 1.0.
Returns:
The class name of the object the property or link belongs to, or the class name of the class the property or links definer belongs to.

getDefiner

public java.lang.Object getDefiner()
The definer is not set by the framework; you can use this to store the definer in your own adapters, if you wish. The default ReaderAdapter uses the definer to store the definer in the getType method so it is not looked up again after setting the value.

getModel

public XMIFile.Model getModel()
If there is a namespace for the feature, and the namespace name matches the name of a model in the header of an XML header, the model is set; otherwise, this method returns null.
Returns:
Null or the model the feature is defined in

getNamespace

public Namespace getNamespace()
If there is a namespace for the feature, the XML namespace is set. You can get the namespace name and namespace uri from the namespace object that is returned.
Returns:
Null or the namespace

getObject

public java.lang.Object getObject()
Returns:
The object returned from the createObject method that the feature belongs to.

getValue

public java.lang.Object getValue()
Returns:
Either an object for an object property or a string for a basic property.
